"from\": 562, \"to\": 573}, {\"ngram\": \"a purpose\", \"from\": 654, \"to\": 663}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games symbolise extravagance\", \"from\": 670, \"to\": 702}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris 2024 has sought to minimise new construction.\", \"from\": 706, \"to\": 757, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 706, \"end\": 716, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5204909683914832e-21, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"new construction\", \"from\": 740, \"to\": 756}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Almost all venues use existing or temporary sites, often relying on the city's landmarks as backdrops.\", \"from\": 759, \"to\": 861, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Almost all venues\", \"from\": 759, \"to\": 776}, {\"ngram\": \"existing or temporary sites\", \"from\": 781, \"to\": 808}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's landmarks\", \"from\": 827, \"to\": 847}, {\"ngram\": \"backdrops\", \"from\": 851, \"to\": 860}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organisers say the replacement of concrete with low carbon building materials, including sustainably-sourced wood, will reduce the Olympic Village's emissions by 30% compared to what the organisers referred to as conventional projects without giving details.\", \"from\": 863, \"to\": 1121, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 994, \"end\": 1009, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.285773115590006e-15, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Organisers\", \"from\": 863, \"to\": 873}, {\"ngram\": \"the replacement\", \"from\": 878, \"to\": 893}, {\"ngram\": \"concrete\", \"from\": 897, \"to\": 905}, {\"ngram\": \"low carbon building materials\", \"from\": 911, \"to\": 940}, {\"ngram\": \"sustainably-sourced wood\", \"from\": 952, \"to\": 976}, {\"ngram\": \"30%\", \"from\": 1025, \"to\": 1028}, {\"ngram\": \"the organisers\", \"from\": 1046, \"to\": 1060}, {\"ngram\": \"conventional projects\", \"from\": 1076, \"to\": 1097}, {\"ngram\": \"details\", \"from\": 1113, \"to\": 1120}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Permanent infrastructure accounted for 73% of the estimated 467,000 tonnes of carbon emissions generated by the Olympic Games between 2018 and 2023.\", \"from\": 1123, \"to\": 1271, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Permanent infrastructure\", \"from\": 1123, \"to\": 1147}, {\"ngram\": \"73%\", \"from\": 1162, \"to\": 1165}, {\"ngram\": \"the estimated 467,000 tonnes\", \"from\": 1169, \"to\": 1197}, {\"ngram\": \"carbon emissions\", \"from\": 1201, \"to\": 1217}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1231, \"to\": 1248}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition, 11,000 seats at the only two purpose-built arenas for Paris 2024 are made out of recycled plastic.\", \"from\": 1273, \"to\": 1384, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1340, \"end\": 1350, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5204909683914832e-21, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"addition\", \"from\": 1276, \"to\": 1284}, {\"ngram\": \"11,000 seats\", \"from\": 1286, \"to\": 1298}, {\"ngram\": \"the only two purpose-built arenas\", \"from\": 1302, \"to\": 1335}, {\"ngram\": \"recycled plastic\", \"from\": 1367, \"to\": 1383}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Transport Along with construction, transport is expected to be one of the biggest sources of emissions during the event.\", \"from\": 1386, \"to\": 1507, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"construction\", \"from\": 1407, \"to\": 1419}, {\"ngram\": \"transport\", \"from\": 1421, \"to\": 1430}, {\"ngram\": \"the biggest sources\", \"from\": 1456, \"to\": 1475}, {\"ngram\": \"emissions\", \"from\": 1479, \"to\": 1488}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 1496, \"to\": 1505}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organisers have said they will use low-carbon vehicles to ferry around athletes and official visitors and that all venues are accessible by bike, foot or public transport.\", \"from\": 1509, \"to\": 1680, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Organisers\", \"from\": 1509, \"to\": 1519}, {\"ngram\": \"low-carbon vehicles\", \"from\": 1544, \"to\": 1563}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1580, \"to\": 1588}, {\"ngram\": \"official visitors\", \"from\": 1593, \"to\": 1610}, {\"ngram\": \"all venues\", \"from\": 1620, \"to\": 1630}, {\"ngram\": \"bike\", \"from\": 1649, \"to\": 1653}, {\"ngram\": \"foot\", \"from\": 1655, \"to\": 1659}, {\"ngram\": \"public transport\", \"from\": 1663, \"to\": 1679}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, Paris is not tackling the emissions generated by spectators travelling to the Games.\", \"from\": 1682, \"to\": 1775, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1691, \"end\": 1696, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1186626405116135e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the emissions\", \"from\": 1713, \"to\": 1726}, {\"ngram\": \"spectators\", \"from\": 1740, \"to\": 1750}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1765, \"to\": 1774}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Such emissions made up almost a third (28%) of the 3.3 million tonnes of carbon emitted by the London 2012 Games.\", \"from\": 1777, \"to\": 1890, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1872, \"end\": 1889, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"London 2012 Games\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \